, break with wasteful traditional practice, utilize agencies and arrangements beyond the school building, and design each child’s educational program around his or her particular needs and potential.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEducation, SecondaryzUnited States. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Educators.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010458540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012851240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300128512423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300128512/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY